.TH DIRNAME(1),User Commands,DIRNAME(1)

.SH NAME
dirname - strip the last component from a pathname

.SH SYNOPSIS
dirname string [string ...]

.SH DESCRIPTION
dirname prints the directory portion of each string.
For each argument, trailing slashes are removed, then the final slash-delimited component is stripped, and any remaining trailing slashes are removed again.

If the resulting string would be empty, a single slash is printed when the input began with slashes, and a single dot is printed otherwise.

If the input is exactly //, the implementation prints // (preserved).

Each result is printed on its own line.

.SH EXAMPLES
$ dirname /usr/bin/sort

 /usr/bin

$ dirname stdio.h

 .

$ dirname /

 /

$ dirname /usr/local/ include/stdio.h

 /usr
 include

.SH EXIT STATUS
0: At least one operand was processed.

1: No operand was given.
